  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-bacon-amatriciana-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-bacon-amatriciana-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh orecchiette </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>orecchiette</strong> for 4-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>orecchiette</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-bacon-amatriciana-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, slice your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-bacon-amatriciana-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon lardons have started to brown, add the<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong>,<strong> sliced garlic</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-bacon-amatriciana-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly – this is your <strong>Amatriciana sauce</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-bacon-amatriciana-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained orecchiette </strong>to the pan and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce – this is your <strong>tomato & bacon Amatriciana sauce with fresh orecchiette</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tomato-and-bacon-amatriciana-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomato & bacon Amatriciana sauce with fresh orecchiette</strong> topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
